io.odysz.semantic.jprotocol

Class JMessage<T extends JBody>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.odysz.semantic.jprotocol.JMessage<T>

  • public class JMessage<T extends JBody>
extends Object

    Base class of message used by JProtocol.

    Relationship with SemanticObject:

    1. A incoming json message is parsed by *.serv into JMessage, which should used to directly build statement;
    2. A outgoing data ojbect is presented as SemanticObject, which should been directly write int output stream.
    Author:
    odys-z@github.com

      static void understandPorts(IPort p)
      Set the default IPort implelemtation, which is used for parsing port name (string) to IPort instance, like JMessage.Port.
      Because {JMessage.Port only defined limited ports, user must initialize JMessage with understandPorts(IPort).
      An example of how to use this is shown in jserv-sample/io.odysz.jsample.SysMenu.
      Also check how to implement IPort extending JMessage.Port, see example of jserv-sample/io.odysz.jsample.protocol.Samport.
